The people working the desk could have been swamped with a hundred people checking in at once and they are just as eager to help the next person or to recommend a spot to eat.	The staff was unassuming but very friendly and efficient, and they were genuinely trying to help and not pushing for tips.	We arrived after 11 PM and the nice guy at the front desk, George, took note of our quiet-room request and searched for changes he could make to the room assignment.	All staff were so friendly, all the time, ready to help and eager to hear about your day.